data.title: Jax - "Crazy Ex Girlfriend"
data.meta_description: Premiered during her performance at the Big Time Rush concert
data.text:
Post by RoseColoredGirl on

I enjoyed "Victoria's Secret" and "Cinderella Snapped," but I admittedly was not the biggest fan of this one. I am not usually one to say that songs are dated, because I don't believe that a song feeling like a part of a different era means they are no longer enjoyable. However, whereas "Victoria's Secret" and "Cinderella Snapped" felt like they had a modern touch to them with a hint of Avril Lavigne/Paramore-like pop-punk, this feels like it channels 2000s pop-punk a little too hard, and not in a good way. It was a bit hard to hear her voice at points because the instruments were much louder than her vocals, so who knows, maybe I'll like it better if/when the studio version is released. However, as of this moment, I can't say I'm a fan of this and hopefully she isn't planning on releasing this as the next single.
